cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on privacy preservation in an outsourced k-NN system, which is a security concern. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The k-NN algorithm is a popular classification algorithm and falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper discusses the storage and computational requirements of k-NN, which are related to database management. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a privacy-preserving alternative system supporting kernel density estimation, which is a machine learning algorithm. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The k-NN algorithm is a part of the family of artificial intelligence algorithms, and the paper proposes an alternative algorithm from the same family.
